          },
          "blocks": {
            "accordion_row_phRkaY": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What are Adult Diapers?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_4DCnMq": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Adult Diaper is an absorbent hygiene product designed to manage urinary or bowel incontinence in adults. </p><p>Adult diapers are designed for both men and women who are not able to control urine movement due to any medical or age-related issue.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_4DCnMq"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_WQp76U": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What is Urinary Incontinence (UI)?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_TjbcWP": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Urinary Incontinence is the loss of control over the bladder or bowel that makes the person need to urinate frequently, have sudden urges or leak accidentally.<br/></p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_TjbcWP"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_tB7mPC": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What are various causes of Urinary Incontinence?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_wmdR76": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Common causes include: Ageing, Diabetes, Neurological disorders, post-surgery recovery. Due to age or any<br/>medical condition, urine leakages can happen in elders even upon coughing, laughing or sneezing. Sudden<br/>intense urge to urinate or bladder not emptying fully can also be reasons for UI.<br/>Women face Urinary Incontinence problems more than men due to various gender related issues like<br/>pregnancy & childbirth, Menopause, being more prone to urinary tract infections & weaker pelvic floor<br/>muscles.<br/>Men also have gender specific issues like prostate enlargement which weaken bladder control.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_wmdR76"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_Uw93CP": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What material is used in the adult diaper?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_wgNdWd": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>They are made from soft, breathable non-woven fabric inner layers, PE barrier films to prevent leakage and<br/>Super Absorbent Polymer (SAP) that instantly converts liquid into gel within minutes, thereby giving the<br/>person a dry feel even when a diaper is used.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_wgNdWd"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_yCRV33": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What are the types of adult diapers available?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_VV4m8n": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Adult diapers are mainly available in two types: Pants style Adult Diaper (Pull-Up) & Adult Diaper Tape Style<br/>Diapers. Each type of adult diapers caters to different mobility and bed-ridden care requirements. Pull Up<br/>pants, as suggested by the name, can simply be pulled up the legs like wearing any normal underwear. But<br/>Tape Style Diapers come with side tapes. These are mostly used for bed-ridden patients & are mostly made<br/>to wea, by the care-givers.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_VV4m8n"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_aBc123": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What is the Difference between Tape and Pant style Diaper?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_XyZ456": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Tape style is primarily used for bedridden patients, while Pant style is more used for active, mobile users<br/>affected by a weak urine bladder. But mostly these are the patients who can pull up a diaper easily, by themselves.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_XyZ456"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_DeF789": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "How do I choose the right size?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_GhI012": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Choosing the correct size is the most important aspect from leak protection & comfort perspective. Measure<br/>your waist size and refer to the size chart provided on the pack. A snug fit works best. It is important to<br/>ensure that the diaper is hugging the thighs well.<br/>If the diaper is slightly loose on the thighs, then a smaller size should be used.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_GhI012"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_JkL345": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Do TULIPS adult diapers control odour?",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "hide_if_empty": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_MnO678": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Yes. ‘Odour Lock’ molecules present in Super Absorbent Polymer (SAP) helps neutralize unpleasant urine<br/>smell and keeps you feeling fresh and confident. TULIPS adult diaper pants are designed to neutralize odour-<br/>causing bacteria giving extended freshness to the wearer.</p>",
                    "enable_read_more": false,
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
